HEADWORD: Redisseizin
<hw>Re`dis*sei"zin</hw> <pr>(-s?"z?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A disseizin by one who once before was adjudged to
have dassezed the same person of the same lands, etc.; also, a writ
which lay in such a case.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redisseizor</ent>⟦br⟧
